body:
Before:

```rust
pub trait InboundUpgrade<C>: UpgradeInfo {
    // ...
    fn upgrade_inbound(self, socket: Negotiated<C>, info: Self::Info) -> Self::Future;
}
```

After:

```rust
pub trait InboundUpgrade<C>: UpgradeInfo {
    // ...
    fn upgrade_inbound(self, socket: C, info: Self::Info) -> Self::Future;
}
```

(same for `OutboundUpgrade`)

This PR removes the `Negotiated` wrapper passed to upgrade, and instead moves this `Negotiated` to the trait bound requirements.

In addition to making it cleaner, the underlying motivation is that once you have a `Negotiated<impl AsyncRead>`, it is very hard to turn it into a `Negotiated<Box<dyn AsyncRead>>`.
While you can of course turn the entire `Negotiated<...>` into a `Box<dyn AsyncRead>`, this is not an option if you want to leverage an underlying upgrade that expects a `Negotiated<...>` to be passed.
